Justice Diana Bryant has said commercial surrogacy should be legalised in Australia . 
  She said Australian women should be able to choose to be a surrogate mother . 
  Justice Bryant said the laws need to be overhauled to prevent cases of abandonment . 
  She was speaking at the University of Queensland on Friday . 
  This week an Australian couple left a baby boy born to a surrogate in Thailand . 
  The couple left the baby and his twin sister behind in India . 
  Baby Gammy was born in Thailand to a Thai surrogate . 
 